<collectingDate id="0A540B2EFFA8561CCEEFFD7A0A43FD49" box="[136,355,662,688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" value="2019-11-10">10 November 2019</collectingDate>
</date>
, 
<collectorName id="C35BB1D0FFA8561CCF09FD7A0AC5FD48" box="[366,485,662,689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Hai X. Ma</collectorName>
(FCATAS 846)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E11D406FFA8561CCEDAFD560F33FBC5" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,1337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCEDAFD560BDFFD2D" bold="true" box="[189,255,698,724]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Note:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCF7CFD560AD6FD2D" box="[283,502,698,724]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="larissae">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCF7CFD560AD6FD2D" box="[283,502,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Hypoxylon larissae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its effused-pulvinate stromata, conspicuous perithecial mounds, Orange (7) and Luteous (12) pigments extracted in 10% KOH, amyloid apical apparatus, light brown to dark brown ascospores with straight germ slit and perispore dehiscent. In both morphological and phylogenetic aspects, the new species seems to be very similar and close to 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCC19FCCB09CEFCB9" box="[638,750,806,832]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fenderi">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCC19FCCB09CEFCB9" box="[638,750,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. fenderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(bootstrap value = 96%/87%/1; 
<figureCitation id="F695C883FFA8561CCA3FFCCA0FB8FCB9" box="[1112,1176,806,832]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,621,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-211@5.[151,1436,602,1926]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic tree of Hypoxylon based on the multigene alignment of ITS-LSU-RPB2-TUB2 in the Maximum Likelihood analyses (RaxML). Support values of Maximum Likelihood (ML), Maximum Parsimony (MP) and Bayesian (B) analyses (bootstrap support above 50%, posterior probability value above 0.95) are displayed above or below the respective branches (ML/MP/BA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6336777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6336777/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), which has both similar perithecia [obovoid, 0.2–0.4 (–0.5) mm broad × 
<quantity id="A95679E3FFA8561CCCD5FCA6081BFC9C" box="[690,827,842,869]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.6 mm</quantity>
high] and KOH-extractable pigment Orange (7) (
<bibRefCitation id="0A3FA9F7FFA8561CCB14FCA60A3FFC70" author="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D." pageId="7" pageNumber="220" refId="ref7324" refString="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D. (1996) A revision of the genus Hypoxylon. American Phytopathological Society Press, St. Paul, Minnesota." type="book" year="1996">Ju &amp; Rogers 1996</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCF51FC820929FC71" box="[310,521,878,904]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fenderi">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCF51FC820929FC71" box="[310,521,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Hypoxylon fenderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCD1CFC8208D1FC71" box="[891,1009,878,904]" name="Venezuela" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and commonly found throughout the tropics. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCFEFFC7F0924FC55" box="[392,516,914,940]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="larissae">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCFEFFC7F0924FC55" box="[392,516,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. larissae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having smaller apical apparatus (0.5–1.2 µm high × 1.8–2.5 µm broad), smaller ascospores (9–12 × 4–5.5 µm) and sigmoid germ slit spore-length (
<bibRefCitation id="0A3FA9F7FFA8561CCDE2FC5A0F78FC28" author="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D." box="[901,1112,950,977]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" refId="ref7324" refString="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D. (1996) A revision of the genus Hypoxylon. American Phytopathological Society Press, St. Paul, Minnesota." type="book" year="1996">Ju &amp; Rogers 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Unfortunately, no molecular phylogenetic data have so far been generated for the 
<typeStatus id="B1156AA4FFA8561CCC85FC360864FC0D" box="[738,836,986,1012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCD0BFC3708FEFC0D" box="[876,990,986,1012]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fenderi">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCD0BFC3708FEFC0D" box="[876,990,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. fenderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The work accomplished by 
<bibRefCitation id="0A3FA9F7FFA8561CCB4EFC360BF5FBE0" author="Hsieh, H. &amp; Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D. &amp; Hsieh, H. &amp; Rogers, J. D." pageId="7" pageNumber="220" pagination="844 - 865" refId="ref6747" refString="Hsieh, H., Ju, Y. M., Rogers, J. D., Hsieh, H. &amp; Rogers, J. D. (2005) Molecular phylogeny of Hypoxylon and closely related genera. Mycologia 97: 844 - 865. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 15572536.2006.11832776" type="journal article" year="2005">
Hsieh 
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCB15FC370E8CFC0D" box="[1394,1452,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">et al.</emphasis>
(2005)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0A3FA9F7FFA8561CCE87FC120AAFFBE1" author="Sir, E. B. &amp; Becker, K. &amp; Lambert, C. &amp; Bills, G. F. &amp; Kuhnert, E." box="[224,399,1022,1048]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" pagination="832 - 856" refId="ref8383" refString="Sir, E. B., Becker, K., Lambert, C., Bills, G. F. &amp; Kuhnert, E. (2019) Observations on Texas hypoxylons, including two new Hypoxylon species and widespread environmental isolates of the H. croceum complex identified by a polyphasic approach. Mycologia 11: 832 - 856. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.2019.1637705" type="journal article" year="2019">
Sir 
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCF60FC130A1EFBE1" box="[263,318,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="0A3FA9F7FFA8561CCFA3FC120988FBE1" author="Cedeno &amp; Sanchez, M. &amp; Wendt, L. &amp; Stadler, M. &amp; Mejia, L. C." box="[452,680,1022,1048]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" pagination="1457 - 1476" refId="ref6098" refString="Cedeno - Sanchez, M., Wendt, L., Stadler, M. &amp; Mejia, L. C. (2020) Three new species of Hypoxylon and new records of Xylariales from Panama. Mycosphere 11: 1457 - 1476. https: // doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 11 / 1 / 9" type="journal article" year="2020">
Cedeno 
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCC78FC130977FBE1" box="[543,599,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
provided additional 
<collectionCode id="08BF4CC3FFA8561CCDEAFC12089AFBE1" box="[909,954,1022,1048]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">ITS</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="08BF4CC3FFA8561CCDA2FC1208DDFBE1" box="[965,1021,1022,1048]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15590" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15590" name="Louisiana State University - Herbarium" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" type="Herbarium">LSU</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="08BF4CC3FFA8561CCA60FC120F1DFBE1" box="[1031,1085,1022,1048]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">RPB</collectionCode>
2 and TUB2 sequence data of the species from 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCF7AFBCE0A55FBC5" box="[285,373,1058,1084]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCFE6FBCE0A97FBC5" box="[385,439,1058,1084]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">USA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCF89FBCF0967FBC4" box="[494,583,1059,1085]" name="Panama" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Panama</collectingCountry>
respectively, was used in our phylogeny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E11D406FFA8561CCEDAFBAA0E40FAC1" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,1337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">
Microscopically, 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCFE3FBAB0923FB99" box="[388,515,1094,1120]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="larissae">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCFE3FBAB0923FB99" box="[388,515,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. larissae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCCB9FBAB08CDFB99" authority="Rehm" authorityName="Rehm" box="[734,1005,1094,1120]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="diatrypeoides">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCCB9FBAB08BCFB99" box="[734,924,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. diatrypeoides</emphasis>
Rehm
</taxonomicName>
, both of which have the same size of ascospores with straight germ slit spore-length, perispore dehiscent in 10% KOH. However, the 
<typeStatus id="B1156AA4FFA8561CCA98FB860E41FB7D" box="[1279,1377,1130,1156]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCBF7FB870A00FB51" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="diatrypeoides">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCBF7FB870A00FB51" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. diatrypeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCF0FFB620A8CFB51" box="[360,428,1166,1192]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Brazil</collectingCountry>
has restrictedly pulvinate stromata and bluing apical apparatus or not in Melzer’s reagent (
<bibRefCitation id="0A3FA9F7FFA8561CCEF7FB5E0A7EFB34" author="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D." box="[144,350,1202,1229]" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" refId="ref7324" refString="Ju, Y. M. &amp; Rogers, J. D. (1996) A revision of the genus Hypoxylon. American Phytopathological Society Press, St. Paul, Minnesota." type="book" year="1996">Ju &amp; Rogers 1996</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCFD1FB5F0910FB35" box="[438,560,1202,1228]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="larissae">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCFD1FB5F0910FB35" box="[438,560,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. larissae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has effused-pulvinate stromata and amyloid and discoid apical apparatus bluing in Melzer’s reagent. The phylogenetic analysis showed that 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCD4CFB3B0886FB09" box="[811,934,1238,1264]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="larissae">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCD4CFB3B0886FB09" box="[811,934,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. larissae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCD8CFB3A0F0EFB09" box="[1003,1070,1238,1264]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">China</collectingCountry>
is distantly related to the clade of 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCEEFFB170A64FAED" box="[136,324,1274,1300]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="diatrypeoides">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCEEFFB170A64FAED" box="[136,324,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. diatrypeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCFEAFB160AC3FAED" box="[397,483,1274,1300]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Mexico</collectingCountry>
in the phylogram (
<figureCitation id="F695C883FFA8561CCCD9FB16083FFAED" box="[702,799,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,621,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-211@5.[151,1436,602,1926]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic tree of Hypoxylon based on the multigene alignment of ITS-LSU-RPB2-TUB2 in the Maximum Likelihood analyses (RaxML). Support values of Maximum Likelihood (ML), Maximum Parsimony (MP) and Bayesian (B) analyses (bootstrap support above 50%, posterior probability value above 0.95) are displayed above or below the respective branches (ML/MP/BA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6336777" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6336777/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). The other specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCA25FB170FDEFAED" box="[1090,1278,1274,1300]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="diatrypeoides">
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCA25FB170FDEFAED" box="[1090,1278,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">H. diatrypeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from 
<collectingCountry id="16B99496FFA8561CCEEFFAF30A3EFAC1" box="[136,286,1310,1337]" name="New Zealand" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
might be a different taxon, so our comparison was based on the type species of 
<emphasis id="5CDA0814FFA8561CCAF9FAF30E40FAC1" box="[1182,1376,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicName id="A9AEAF85FFA8561CCAF9FAF30E7CFAC1" box="[1182,1372,1310,1336]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Hypoxylon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="7" pageNumber="220" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="diatrypeoides">H. diatrypeoides</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
